  "instructions": [
    "Melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the sliced onion and cook until it is caramelized, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Stir in the all-purpose flour and cook for 1-2 minutes, until it is lightly toasted.",
    "Gradually stir in the fish stock, whisking continuously to avoid lumps.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes, until the soup has thickened.",
    "Stir in the heavy cream and soured cream, and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, until the soup has heated through.",
    "Season the soup with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "If desired, add in some grated cheddar cheese, malt vinegar, or malted milk powder for extra flavor.",
    "Serve the soup hot, topped with chopped chives and a dollop of soured cream.",
    "Optional: Add in some diced fish, such as cod, haddock, or tilapia, for added protein and flavor.",
    "Optional: Top the soup with some chopped scallions, crumbled bacon, or crispy onions for added texture and flavor.",
    "Optional: Serve the soup with some crusty bread or crackers for dipping into the soured cream and chive dip.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving.",
    "Cook pork to an internal temperature of 63°C / 145°F and let it rest for 3 minutes before serving."
  ],
